2015-06-09 15:12:18	marshmn	ldlework: how do you handle editing your files?
2015-06-09 15:12:27	cpuguy83	I really wish something like overlay (And bind-mounts generally) supported uid re-mapping.
2015-06-09 15:12:30	-->	superguenter (~Adium@199.116.75.18) has joined #docker
2015-06-09 15:12:33	@ldlework	marshmn: I put the most volitile files at the end of my dockerfile so that rebuilding the image only takes a moment.
2015-06-09 15:12:35	-->	seanmcl (~seanmcl@69.64.193.242) has joined #docker
2015-06-09 15:12:46	@ldlework	[system][stack deps][my code]
2015-06-09 15:12:50	marshmn	ah, so you rebuild after every code change
2015-06-09 15:12:59	vdemeester	marshmn: I tend to either not caring to much (editing is fine, it won't modifiy the owner), but if it creates files, I tend to make my image with a user that has the same id as my local user
2015-06-09 15:13:07	marshmn	ldlework: that sounds a bit painful though?
2015-06-09 15:13:16	@ldlework	marshmn: it takes about 4 seconds
