2015-06-10 12:22:50	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: Issue here is likely with how devmapper and docker are installed.
2015-06-10 12:23:19	<--	moonflux (~mss@slpn-nb-mss.desy.de) has quit (Remote host closed the connection)
2015-06-10 12:23:21	detach-	cpuguy83: what different is it from me deploying a new windows vm pre-installed with exchange?
2015-06-10 12:24:07	detach-	cpuguy83: still puzzling :(
2015-06-10 12:24:08	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: devicemapper (as we've learned recently) is required to be dynamically so it can talk to udev properly... and likewise docker itself needs to be a dynbinary since it needs to talk to devmapper.
2015-06-10 12:24:34	gchristensen	that is annoying
2015-06-10 12:24:55	-->	zhitao (~zhitao@4.53.133.222) has joined #docker
2015-06-10 12:24:56	-->	njero (~njero@100.32.79.209) has joined #docker
2015-06-10 12:25:03	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: Docker itself is statically compiled, with devmapper, if you've installed it from the main docker repo
2015-06-10 12:25:09	detach-	cpuguy83: i'm reading http://www.quora.com/What-is-the-purpose-of-Docker
2015-06-10 12:25:38	foist	Is `--entrypoint=“”` the `docker run` analog of docker-compose’s `command` instruction?
2015-06-10 12:25:58	aristarchus_	cpuguy83: on my AWS setup, the AMI is derived from the (latest) Canonical Ubuntu UEC 14.04 LTS images, so udev comes from there. DOcker (1.6.2) is being installed from the .deb packages at https://get.docker.com/ubuntu
2015-06-10 12:26:20	vdemeester	foist: command == CMD, entrypoint == ENTRYPOINT (I guess entrypoint is supported in docker-compose.yml)
2015-06-10 12:26:28	-->	MikaAK (~mikaak@S0106789684be0c51.vc.shawcable.net) has joined #docker
2015-06-10 12:26:56	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: Yeah, that's the problem.
2015-06-10 12:27:15	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: I'd recommend using aufs if you can (just need to install the linux-image-extra package)
2015-06-10 12:27:34	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: devicemapper is horrid, even with a proper setup.
2015-06-10 12:27:36	foist	vdemeester: thanks :)
2015-06-10 12:28:04	-->	jhuet (~Jeremy@mail.nextep.fr) has joined #docker
2015-06-10 12:28:21	aristarchus_	cpuguy83: Thanks for the info -- I'm new to how docker uses its storage layer - are there docs on how to alter my setup for AUFS?
2015-06-10 12:28:45	<--	michael_mbp (~michael_m@173.255.242.136) has quit (Excess Flood)
2015-06-10 12:29:16	-->	the_real_intinig (~intinig@93-51-152-125.ip267.fastwebnet.it) has joined #docker
2015-06-10 12:29:19	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: edit /etc/default/docker and add `-s aufs` after installing the linux-image-extras package (which includes the aufs stuff)
2015-06-10 12:29:19	-->	donspaulding (~donspauld@107.152.3.83) has joined #docker
2015-06-10 12:29:19	-->	odinnap (~Adium@207.104.28.51) has joined #docker
2015-06-10 12:29:38	aristarchus_	Thanks a bunch -- will try it out
2015-06-10 12:29:42	cpuguy83	aristarchus_: On a fresh daemon start, if aufs is available, docker will just use that.
