2015-06-11 12:15:41	pitiye	guys i made docker instance using ubuntu and installed lamp stack manually,  after that i looked into /var/cache/apt/ and it was empty , is this an expected behavior ?
2015-06-11 12:16:34	<--	superguenter (~Adium@199.116.75.18) has quit (Quit: Leaving.)
2015-06-11 12:16:52	-->	parallel21 (~finn@162.243.212.98) has joined #docker
2015-06-11 12:18:03	<--	frasergraham (~frasergra@17.115.0.92) has quit (Ping timeout: 276 seconds)
2015-06-11 12:18:03	eljrax	pitiye: It's not expected to install a full lamp stack in a single container, no
2015-06-11 12:18:04	<--	thebishop (~thebishop@50.243.39.109) has quit (Ping timeout: 272 seconds)
2015-06-11 12:18:33	<--	fluter (~fluter@fedora/fluter) has quit (Ping timeout: 244 seconds)
2015-06-11 12:18:47	-->	Freman (~twitsrus@2a00:1768:1004::1e7a:74e9) has joined #docker
2015-06-11 12:19:07	pitiye	eljrax:  yes i understand - i just needed a testbed for a little app , that is why i did so
2015-06-11 12:19:25	<--	parallel21 (~finn@162.243.212.98) has left #docker ("Textual IRC Client: www.textualapp.com")
2015-06-11 12:19:47	eljrax	pitiye: To answer your question.. if you used the ubuntu base image, that is expected
2015-06-11 12:20:01	eljrax	Check /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/docker-clean
2015-06-11 12:20:05	eljrax	It's to keep images small
2015-06-11 12:20:28	-->	Goopyo (~Goopyo@50.245.28.10) has joined #docker
2015-06-11 12:20:31	<--	rossriley (~Adium@85.105.31.66) has quit (Quit: Leaving.)
2015-06-11 12:20:36	<--	eddd (~eddd@185.32.152.150) has quit (Read error: Connection reset by peer)
2015-06-11 12:20:44	pitiye	eljrax: ah , got it
2015-06-11 12:20:48	-->	eddd (~eddd@185.32.152.150) has joined #docker
2015-06-11 12:21:23	pitiye	eljrax:   i was looking for a way to reduce my internet bandwidth - by saving all the apt cache and copy it into other instances :D
2015-06-11 12:21:34	<--	eikeon (~textual@98.218.4.80) has quit (Quit: My Mac has gone to sleep. ZZZzzz…)
2015-06-11 12:21:43	pitiye	i know its a cheap way of doing things ,  but at least it solves my problem ;)
2015-06-11 12:22:16	eljrax	Well that's alright :) Just remove that file, and you'll have the archives left
2015-06-11 12:22:28	-->	obto (~naruze@c-50-151-127-18.hsd1.il.comcast.net) has joined #docker
2015-06-11 12:23:03	eljrax	pitiye: You can set /var/cache/apt as a volume, and share that between future containers
2015-06-11 12:24:37	pitiye	eljrax:  i have this https://github.com/jpetazzo/squid-in-a-can
2015-06-11 12:24:43	-->	firecat53 (~firecat53@c-50-135-49-6.hsd1.wa.comcast.net) has joined #docker
