2015-06-11 13:48:58	foist	ldlework:a while ago you advised to have an ADD instruction as the last line of my Dockerfile, which would add the source folder. When changes are made to the source, the image would be rebuilt with everything but the last step being cached. Why is this advisable over mounting the source as a volume?
2015-06-11 13:49:00	IvanSuftin	detach-: the other thing you could do if you want to get operational precision on killing your container processes without killing your container woul be to open another terminal and do "docker exec -it [cid] /bin/bash"
