2015-06-12 08:59:37	<--	jasondotstar (~jasondots@173.38.117.74) has quit (Remote host closed the connection)
2015-06-12 09:00:04	PaulePanter	Hmm, looking at `/var/log/upstart/docker-containers.log` there is.
2015-06-12 09:00:04	<--	jnahelou (~jnahelou@77.242.202.235) has quit (Client Quit)
2015-06-12 09:00:04	PaulePanter	Post http:///var/run/docker.sock/v1.14/containers/postgresql/start: dial unix /var/run/docker.sock: no such file or directory
2015-06-12 09:00:12	-->	tiagoboldt (~tiagobold@193.137.28.184) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 09:00:15	-->	Error404NotFound (~Error404N@unaffiliated/error404notfound) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 09:00:31	PaulePanter	Why is the socket not there yet, when the Upstart file specifies `start on filesystem and started docker`?
2015-06-12 09:00:33	-->	stlalpha (~jm@12.160.138.2) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 09:01:01	<--	moos3 (~moos3@63.251.83.162) has quit (Ping timeout: 264 seconds)
2015-06-12 09:02:07	<--	bfoote (foobar@eidolon.bnf.net) has quit (Ping timeout: 248 seconds)
2015-06-12 09:02:27	PaulePanter	Ok, looks like it’s a problem, a lot of people experience. Let me see what the solution is.
2015-06-12 09:02:34	-->	balazs (~balazs@97-118-61-21.hlrn.qwest.net) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 09:02:49	--	dims is now known as dimsum__
2015-06-12 09:03:11	-->	paulweb515 (~pwebster@eclipse/developer/Eclipse/paulweb515) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 09:03:14	-->	bfoote (foobar@eidolon.bnf.net) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 09:03:28	gchristensen	PaulePanter: add a bit of a retry delay, it may be that the docker daemon isn't fully started yet
2015-06-12 09:03:41	<--	pjoe (~quassel@207.140.26.138) has quit (Remote host closed the connection)
2015-06-12 09:04:02	<--	alunduil (~alunduil@gentoo/developer/alunduil) has quit (Quit: Leaving)
2015-06-12 09:06:16	--	zz_rabisg is now known as rabisg
2015-06-12 09:06:34	PaulePanter	gchristensen: Yeah, but that is an ugly hack.
2015-06-12 09:06:44	gchristensen	no it isn't
2015-06-12 09:06:51	PaulePanter	I am currently reading https://github.com/docker/docker/issues/6647 .
2015-06-12 09:07:05	gchristensen	if it is an ugly hack,delete this line: respawn
2015-06-12 09:07:23	<--	paulweb515 (~pwebster@eclipse/developer/Eclipse/paulweb515) has quit (Ping timeout: 258 seconds)
2015-06-12 09:07:24	gchristensen	as it stands you're respawning immediately after failure
2015-06-12 09:07:27	gchristensen	add a 1s delay and it should be fine
2015-06-12 09:07:31	PaulePanter	gchristensen: Depending on the state of the universe, only infinity is the right delay.
2015-06-12 09:07:31	<--	balazs (~balazs@97-118-61-21.hlrn.qwest.net) has quit (Ping timeout: 276 seconds)
2015-06-12 09:07:35	gchristensen	yes
2015-06-12 09:07:42	gchristensen	and it will fail eventually
2015-06-12 09:08:06	gchristensen	but give it a 1s respawn delay and you have a much higher chance of it working
2015-06-12 09:08:08	<--	VeeWee (~VeeWee@94.143.188.0) has quit (Quit: WeeChat 0.4.3)
2015-06-12 09:08:27	gchristensen	or don't, I don't care actually
2015-06-12 09:08:28	PaulePanter	This is Docker 1.2.0~dfsg1-1ubuntu1. Let me see, when that was released.
2015-06-12 09:08:35	gchristensen	last year I think
2015-06-12 09:08:58	PaulePanter	gchristensen: Sorry for me being so impolite. Thank you for the help.
2015-06-12 09:09:06	 *	gchristensen shrugs
2015-06-12 09:09:44	PaulePanter	Ok.
2015-06-12 09:09:53	PaulePanter	The package was released on Wed, 01 Oct 2014 13:24:01 -0500.
