2015-06-12 10:07:35	boucher	it will drift as in, once it gets started it will drift
2015-06-12 10:07:41	boucher	or, once the image is built it will drift
2015-06-12 10:07:41	<--	supersheep (~supershee@81.19.48.130) has quit (Read error: Connection reset by peer)
2015-06-12 10:07:42	jacobat	cpuguy83: I don't understand your response to https://github.com/docker/docker/issues/10536 - how is a tarstream different from reading files of the filesystem, both are passing through the client?
2015-06-12 10:07:54	<--	samc_ (~sam@host81-140-195-23.range81-140.btcentralplus.com) has quit (Read error: No route to host)
2015-06-12 10:08:07	boucher	k10d: also i tried installing and running ntpdate but it seems there aren’t enough permissions in the container to set its own time?
2015-06-12 10:08:16	-->	samc_ (~sam@host81-140-195-23.range81-140.btcentralplus.com) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:08:44	k10d	boucher: the images are static so they get stuck, not actually drifting, but the container will drift
2015-06-12 10:08:54	cpuguy83	jacobat: because one way docker is building the context, in which case dockerignore is parsed, in the other you are providing the context, as such you are expected to omit the files you don't want.
2015-06-12 10:09:07	<--	ternagen (~ternagen@130.117.76.198) has quit (Client Quit)
2015-06-12 10:09:09	boucher	k10d: so, what if anything can i do to correct
2015-06-12 10:09:34	cpuguy83	boucher: container's don't have their own time
2015-06-12 10:09:42	cpuguy83	boucher: time is provided by the kernel
2015-06-12 10:09:56	boucher	ok, that’s kind of what i thuoght
2015-06-12 10:10:07	-->	gargola (~quassel@swa01cs006-da02-z.ams.hpecore.net) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:10:12	boucher	so if the host machine’s time is updated the containers should be as well?
2015-06-12 10:10:18	cpuguy83	containers can have their own time zone, but that's all set from the kernel time.
2015-06-12 10:10:22	cpuguy83	yes
2015-06-12 10:11:00	<--	JayFK (~JayFK@p5DE86203.dip0.t-ipconnect.de) has quit (Quit: My MacBook Pro has gone to sleep. ZZZzzz…)
2015-06-12 10:11:07	boucher	ok, thanks.
2015-06-12 10:12:11	-->	rbenevides (~rbenevid@redhat/jboss/RafaelBenevides) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:12:13	-->	adgtl (~anildigit@unaffiliated/anildigital) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:12:57	boucher	i’m trying to track down a twitter authentication issue and my best hope was a system time issue but i’m pretty sure that isn’t it
2015-06-12 10:13:12	k10d	cpuguy83 so why doesn't the containers keep up? http://pastebin.com/m1pFW4X7
2015-06-12 10:13:23	-->	pid1 (~pid1@gateway/vpn/privateinternetaccess/penguinanon) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:13:58	cpuguy83	k10d: Is docker local, in a VM, in a remote host?
2015-06-12 10:14:11	jacobat	cpuguy83: I guess you can view it like that. But would it not be better to just view it as two different ways to provide the context? One is the filesystem another is a tar stream? That would allow for more homogenous treatment and stuff like .dockerignore could be handled uniformly across both.
2015-06-12 10:14:39	jacobat	cpuguy83: At least from the users point of view it's surprising that there is this difference
2015-06-12 10:14:45	Silex	cpuguy83: is "--net=host" & "nginx running on host forwarding to container" the only solutions to "nginx container doesn't see remote ip of clients (only docker ip)" ?
2015-06-12 10:14:47	cpuguy83	jacobat: No, I don't think so. In the case where you provide the tar stream, we expect that is what you want sent to the daemon.
2015-06-12 10:14:59	-->	arunpyasi (~arunpyasi@45.64.160.30) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:14:59	k10d	cpuguy83: ah yes, its boot2docker ...
2015-06-12 10:15:07	jacobat	cpuguy83: Okay
2015-06-12 10:15:12	k10d	nvm me
2015-06-12 10:15:13	cpuguy83	jacobat: Most users don't build their own tars.  If you are building it, you should build it the way you want.
2015-06-12 10:15:33	jacobat	cpuguy83: git archive | docker build
2015-06-12 10:16:03	<--	arunpyasi (~arunpyasi@45.64.160.30) has quit (Max SendQ exceeded)
2015-06-12 10:16:05	cpuguy83	Silex: Hmm, there must be a way to expose the remote IP's... I haven't figured it out either...
2015-06-12 10:16:31	cpuguy83	Silex: Also possibly with 1.7 you will get the correct IP if you use --disable-userland-proxy
2015-06-12 10:16:37	-->	arunpyasi (~arunpyasi@45.64.160.30) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:16:48	Silex	cpuguy83: ah, interesting
2015-06-12 10:16:54	cpuguy83	... or is it userland-proxy-enabled=false
2015-06-12 10:16:55	jacobat	cpuguy83: But yeah sure, I can filter the tar stream, I was just surprised and spent some time figuring out why all of sudden .dockerignore was not taken into account
2015-06-12 10:16:57	cpuguy83	I don't remember
2015-06-12 10:17:24	cpuguy83	jacobat: But what would you `git archive | docker build -` when you can just do `docker build .`
2015-06-12 10:17:26	Silex	cpuguy83: in the meantime, between "net=host" and "host nginx" the latter is preferable right?
2015-06-12 10:17:36	Silex	for production
2015-06-12 10:17:40	cpuguy83	Silex: net=host is fine.
2015-06-12 10:17:51	cpuguy83	And faster
2015-06-12 10:17:56	Silex	alright, thanks
2015-06-12 10:18:02	cpuguy83	And you don't have to deal with port forwards and all that.
2015-06-12 10:18:20	jacobat	cpuguy83: Because it's more elegant in some cases. Also it ensures that no bits have been changed between the git commit and the docker image.
2015-06-12 10:18:20	Silex	I'm always a bit nervous with net=host
2015-06-12 10:18:27	Silex	not sure why
2015-06-12 10:18:42	cpuguy83	jacobat: ah, I hadn't thought of that.
2015-06-12 10:18:53	-->	christyp (~christyp@cpe-70-112-163-90.austin.res.rr.com) has joined #docker
2015-06-12 10:19:28	jacobat	cpuguy83: Like for a build server it might also make sense to just "git archive git@github.com:foo/bar | docker build -"
2015-06-12 10:19:54	cpuguy83	jacobat: Raise the issue with duglin, he's the build master
2015-06-12 10:20:08	jacobat	cpuguy83: Will do, thanks
2015-06-12 10:20:15	jacobat	duglin: ^^ :)
2015-06-12 10:20:50	jacobat	duglin: In short: "docker build ." respects .dockerignore, "docker build -" does not. Confusion arises.
